		<title>In times of recession</title>
		<link>http://www.modula.fi/2008/in-times-of-recession/</link>
		<comments>http://www.modula.fi/2008/in-times-of-recession/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Dec 2008 12:16:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Eero</dc:creator>
		
		<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>

		<category><![CDATA[ads]]></category>

		<category><![CDATA[recession]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.modula.fi/?p=718</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[
In light of the current economic downturn, many small businesses are taking rational steps to protect their business, such as cutting excess costs. Cost cutting is not the only survival strategy, businesses could focus on maintaining current revenue and priming the pump for future business. There have been 32 recessions since 1854, about one every [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.modula.fi/wp-content/uploads/decision.jpg"><img src="http://www.modula.fi/wp-content/uploads/decision.jpg" alt="" title="decision" width="460" height="304" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-724" /></a></p>
<p>In light of the current economic downturn, many small businesses are taking rational steps to protect their business, such as cutting excess costs. Cost cutting is not the only survival strategy, businesses could focus on maintaining current revenue and priming the pump for future business. There have been 32 recessions since 1854, about one every four to five years. And each one offered opportunities for smart businesses.<br />
<span id="more-718"></span><br />
When businesses reduce their investment in marketing and advertising during a recession, their recovery period is much slower when the recession ends. On the other hand, businesses that continue to spend, and even increase their marketing budgets during a recession, recover much faster, gain market share and increase brand&nbsp;awareness.</p>
<p>New products are always certain revenue generators if marketed properly. Determine what sets your business apart from the competition and market it like&nbsp;crazy.</p>
<p>it&#8217;s time to issue live ammo to the sales&nbsp;force:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reactivate old leads and past&nbsp;customers.</li>
<li>Repackage your products and services with offers to&nbsp;act.</li>
<li>Redesign your website with proper&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Search_engine_optimization"><span class="caps">SEO</span></a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Through all of the coming pain, remember one thing: companies never get better at what they do during good times–they just get bigger. Companies only get better at what they do when their survival depends on it–during the bad&nbsp;times.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.modula.fi/2008/in-times-of-recession/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		</item>
