			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://webtypography.net/">The Elements of Typographic Style Applied to the Web</a> is a webzine/book by Richard&nbsp;Rutter:</p>
<blockquote><p>Robert Bringhurst’s book The Elements of Typographic Style is on many a designer’s bookshelf and is considered to be a classic in the field. Indeed the renowned typographer Hermann Zapf proclaims the book to be a must for everybody in the graphic arts, and especially for our new friends entering the&nbsp;field.</p>
<p>In order to allay some of the myths surrounding typography on the web, I have structured this website to step through Bringhurst’s working principles, explaining how to accomplish each using techniques available in html and&nbsp;css.</p></blockquote>
<p>At the time it is a work in progress – the site is being added to one principle at a time. Extremely&nbsp;useful.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
